The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 WBAA on talent hunt 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The West Bengal Athletic Association (WBAA) has taken a bold move for the upliftment of the game in the state from this year. WBAA has asked the districts to shortlist the names of the most talented ones for their better grooming in the city. 

We will talk to Sports Authority of India (SAI), Eastern Centre. If they can accommodate its good, otherwise well (WBAA) bear their expenses, WBAA president Prasun Mukherjee said on Saturday. 

According to Mukherjee, the association will try its best to discover new talent every year during the state meet. 




